thread.title: Magnitude 5.3 quake hits western Iran, no casualties reported - TV

title: Magnitude 5.3 quake hits western Iran, no casualties reported - TV
text:
April 1, 2018 / 9:39 AM / Updated an hour ago Magnitude 5.3 quake hits western Iran, no casualties reported: TV Reuters Staff 1 Min Read 
DUBAI (Reuters) - A magnitude 5.3 earthquake hit western Iran on Sunday, but there were no immediate reports of casualties or damage, state television reported. 
“Up to this moment, ... we have not received any reports of casualties or damage,” Reza Mahmoudian, the head of the crisis management body in the affected province of Kermanshah, told state television. 
A magnitude 7.3 earthquake in the same area in November killed at least 530 people and injured more than 8,000. Reporting by Dubai newsroom; Editing by Mark Potter
